    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's the complete implementation plan for the Ollama rename feature across all 3 layers:\n\n---\n\n### What gets added (7 targeted insertions, nothing modified)\n\n**`api/types.go`** — New `RenameRequest` struct (mirrors `CopyRequest` exactly):\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`api/client.go`** — New `Client.Rename()` method (mirrors `Client.Copy()`, calls `POST /api/rename`):\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    return c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)\n}\n```\n\n**`server/routes.go`** — New `Server.RenameHandler()` with this flow:\n1. Parse + validate JSON body → 400 if missing/empty fields  \n2. `model.ParseName()` + `IsValid()` for both names → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`  \n3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if found → **409 Conflict**  \n4. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — `os.ErrNotExist` → **404**, other error → **500**  \n5. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` → **500** if fails (noting copy succeeded)  \n6. Return **200** `{\"status\":\"success\"}`\n\n**`server/routes.go`** — Register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` right after the `/api/copy` route (line 1698)\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — New `RenameHandler()` function (mirrors `CopyHandler`, prints `Renamed \"src\" to \"dst\"`)\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — New `renameCmd` cobra command (`Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`)\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — Add `renameCmd` to `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` after `copyCmd`",
